## PART 2: Performance & SEO Optimizations

By default, Vite bundles your entire React app into **ONE massive javascript file**. This guarantees a terrible Lighthouse score because the user is forced to download the heavyweight Admin Dashboard code just to view the public landing page.

### 1. React Code Splitting (Lazy Loading)
Instead of synchronously importing components, we wrap them in `React.lazy()` and `<Suspense>`. This brutally chops the application into tiny micro-files.

**Before (Terrible Performance):**
```tsx
import AdminDashboard from "./pages/admin/AdminDashboard";
// The browser downloads AdminDashboard even if the user is on the homepage.
<Route path="admin" element={<AdminDashboard />} />
```

**After (Lightning Fast):**
```tsx
import { lazy, Suspense } from 'react';
const AdminDashboard = lazy(() => import('./pages/admin/AdminDashboard'));

// The browser ONLY downloads AdminDashboard exactly when the user clicks the link.
<Suspense fallback={<LoadingSpinner />}>
    <Route path="admin" element={<AdminDashboard />} />
</Suspense>
```

### 2. Vite Chunk Compression ([vite.config.ts](file:///c:/Users/Great%20Nation/Documents/CalebDeck/vite.config.ts))
We intercept Vite's build algorithm and force it to separate massive library dependencies (like `firebase` and `react`) into their own distinct cached files.

```typescript
export default defineConfig({
  build: {
    rollupOptions: {
      output: {
        manualChunks: {
          'react-vendor': ['react', 'react-dom', 'react-router'],
          'firebase-vendor': ['firebase/app', 'firebase/firestore', 'firebase/auth'],
          'ui-vendor': ['lucide-react', '@radix-ui/react-dialog']
        }
      }
    }
  }
})
```

### 3. Vercel Strict Caching & SPA Rewrites ([vercel.json](file:///c:/Users/Great%20Nation/Documents/CalebDeck/vercel.json))
We force maximum cache-control headers on static assets. Critically, we also implement a SPA Rewrite. If a user tries to access `calebdeck.com/cafeteria` directly, Vercel normally throws a 404 because that file doesn't exist. The rewrite physically forces 100% of traffic to route through React!

```json
{
  "rewrites": [
    {
      "source": "/(.*)",
      "destination": "/index.html"
    }
  ],
  "headers": [
    {
      "source": "/(.*)\\.(css|js|woff2|woff|ttf|svg|jpg|jpeg|png|webp|gif|json|ico)$",
      "headers": [
        {
          "key": "Cache-Control",
          "value": "public, max-age=31536000, immutable"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

### 4. Dynamic SEO with React Helmet (`react-helmet-async`)
Generic titles are bad for SEO. We installed `react-helmet-async` and wrapped the entire React Provider inside `<HelmetProvider>`. Then, we built a reusable `<SEO>` component to dynamically swap `<title>`, `<meta>`, and `og:tags` as the user navigates pages.

Now, instead of "CalebDeck", the About page injects:
`<title>About CalebDeck — Caleb University Campus Delivery</title>`

### 5. LocalBusiness JSON-LD Structured Data
Search engines love machine-readable Code. Inside the `<SEO>` component, we injected a raw `<script type="application/ld+json">` block that formally registers CalebDeck as a LocalBusiness at `addressLocality: Imota` (Caleb University). When someone Googles CalebDeck, this code generates the massive Knowledge Graph card on the right side of Google Search!

### 6. Next-Gen SEO Tags and Bot Masking
We update the [index.html](file:///c:/Users/Great%20Nation/Documents/CalebDeck/index.html) to inject Social Media rich cards. To prevent Google from accidentally indexing the secure Admin tools, we generate a strict [robots.txt](file:///c:/Users/Great%20Nation/Documents/CalebDeck/public/robots.txt) file and a [sitemap.xml](file:///c:/Users/Great%20Nation/Documents/CalebDeck/public/sitemap.xml) file.

**[public/robots.txt](file:///c:/Users/Great%20Nation/Documents/CalebDeck/public/robots.txt)**
```text
User-agent: *
Allow: /
Disallow: /admin
Disallow: /rider

Sitemap: https://calebdeck.com/sitemap.xml
```

**[public/sitemap.xml](file:///c:/Users/Great%20Nation/Documents/CalebDeck/public/sitemap.xml)**
```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<urlset xmlns="http://www.sitemaps.org/schemas/sitemap/0.9">
  <url><loc>https://calebdeck.com/</loc><priority>1.0</priority></url>
  <url><loc>https://calebdeck.com/cafeteria</loc><priority>0.8</priority></url>
</urlset>
```
